TOILET PAPER!

In Saudi Arabia toilet paper is a luxury item!

It almost never available at normal shops, and when you buy it, it’s roofly 200 riyals a 10 toilet roll pack that last about 2 days!

You tend to go to shops that are known as Sani shops because, they dispense toilet roll out of a series of roll like a snooker ball dispenser.

The best public restrooms are darn toilets that you find next to some petrol station, and some have nappy bins to dispose of extra bulky stuff.

Carl McVeigh 

What kind of toilet paper do you use?

Kader Lama 

If I’m at one of home then, it’s the usual brand I’m use to.

If a friend or any where else then, it’s whatever roll they have handy, and it’s usually whatever shop most available near them.

Saudi Arabia, funny but true!

David Watson 

In the East Bay, CA there are immigration forms called 1-765. It has a column that asks you to check the box for what your previous status was. These are government forms.

You cannot check the box if you left the country before your previous visa expired but still have an expired visa. The official answer is you must submit new visa application and if approved to one immigration center.
